						<div class="postbody">Yes, Irfan View is awesome for editing images, I've used that programm for a long time.
<br />
<br />Also thanks tokumaru for clarifying that :
<br />Real life images -&gt; JPEG is better
<br />Pixelised sprites/screenshot -&gt; PNG or GIF is better
<br />I guess PNG and GIF also allow for transparency, while JPEG doesn't. This is usefull when designing a website or something like that, so that you can paste sprites from NES game and keep the transparent color as transparent (altough I wouldn't say my website make a good usage of it).
<br />
<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Which platformers have more realistic graphics, better animation, better special effects in gameplay and an above average designed player to you?</div><br />Castlevania, Mega Man !<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"> BTW, Ryuu is a very uncommon name as it means dragon, and as such is only given to characters having something to do with dragons generally as an alias.</div>
<br />It's a very common name in video games. The main hero of all Breath of Fire games, and the recurent guy in Street Fighter series, are all called that. The hero of Bahamut Lagoon is also called that. Some dragon in Final Fantasy 5 is called that. You really can't call that name uncommon I've seen it hundreds of times (altough it's possible all those times are from games released later than the original NG).
<br />
<br />@Celius : Your upgraded portrait looks really awesome. It's like 100 times better thant he old version. Maybe you should add slightly more shading on the face, other than that it's really perfect.
<br />It's amazing how you became an amazing graphist since this summer. You'll have to tell me how you did that much progress. Now it's me who is going to ask you for help.</div>

					
