<br />
<br />I have been working recently on a tool in dot net to design maps for my future game.  I already decoded chr data to use it on the screen and should be able to save it back soon (I'm planning to integrate a chr editor too).
<br />
<br />You may have a harder time to do it in vb.net because it doesn't support shift operation on bits and you cannot do any unsafe code (if you want to edit the binary data like an array in C, which is a lot faster to do).  If I remember well from your previous posts I think you programmed in c++ before? If you did, I would suggest to do this part in C# if you have some chance, it will be a lot easier.  
<br />
<br />But if for some reason you can't, I could always give you the code I did and make the extra function for converting from a Bitmap class to chr data.  Since you can use compiled c# libraries in VB.NET that shouldn't be a problem.  If for some reason you really want to have all the code in VB, I could always try to port it.  I'm a little bit rusty in vb thought <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />  So I can help you in dot net if you want, ask me anytime.
<br />
<br />By the way Tokumaru, is your avatar coming from the game you're making at the moment? It look great. I would love to see some screen shots of your game someday.
<br />
<br />
<br />Edit: Roth, it may be possible to do it in VB.NET without the need of unsafe mode like C#. It's a little bit more tricky but doable.  And actually, you can do some bit shifting in vb.net since dot net 1.1.  I didn't use vb.net since 1.0 so I thought it was not possible.  I will give it a spin and let you know how it goes.</div>

