					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Oh, Tokumaru, I totally have Photoshop too. The reason I used MS paint for my images was because it's easier for such basic editing. Photoshop is great for lots of things though. I prefer Paint for editing bitmaps.
<br />
<br />I'm glad you like the word Nintendoize, Roth. I claim full rights to making it up! Well, at least I think I was the first to say it in a thread a while ago. If not, I guess I'm not the mastermind. That screenshot looks really cool! It reminds me of GameBoy Camera, which I still have!
<br />
<br />And Bregalad, I'm glad you like my picture so much! Well, this picture was originally a painting. The painting is crap right now, and I still have to fix it. All I really do is shrink the original image down to the appropriate size, trace a black outline over it, and work from there. And I also think long and hard about the palettes I use. These portraits are displayed one per screen, obviously. This portrait uses 2 BG palettes, and 1 sprite palette. But other than that, I just work on graphics when I'm in the right mood. This makes the images I make lots better. I'm glad to hear that someone thinks I'm a good Nintendoizer/graphic artist. It makes me believe more that my game won't turn out with pure garbage graphics.
<br />
<br />I remember when you first showed me the Nintendoization of those 2 FF7 songs, I was completely blown away, as they sounded awesome. When I compared the Mako theme to my version, I felt pretty bad, as mine was made like crap with NT2. Also, your Nintendoization of the Dragon Skill title screen I always thought was really good too.
<br />
<br />Games with above average animation? Batman Return of the Joker! That game has AMAZING graphics in parts. Sprites generally aren't as great as BG textures, as there are less colors to work with (in a sense).
<br />
<br />Now that I look back on it, lots of graphics in the CV games are really bad. There are lots of things that look really cool, but the moss in the games always looked bad to me.
<br />
<br />Oh, and Shinryu is the hardest enemy in FF5 (That means something like Death Dragon, right?), and it will do 8000+ damage if you're not careful. But there's also a "Ryu" I think.</div>

