						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Celius wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Oh, and Shinryu is the hardest enemy in FF5 (That means something like Death Dragon, right?)</div>
<br />Sometimes it's hard to tell what a japanese name means without looking at the kanji, because many different ones are pronounced the same. In this case though, I don't think it means "Death Dragon", because "death" is "shi", not "shin", as far as I can remember. I think "shin" could mean "new" or "real", but don't take my word for it. It's been a while since I studied japanese, and it's not like I get a lot of chances to practice.
<br />
<br />EDIT: I was just thinking about what you said, and in fact there is a Shiryu in an anime I know, called Saint Seiya. Even in his case, the name doesn't mean "Death Dragon", I think it's "Purple Dragon". Again, don't take my word for it! =)</div>

